<L>__{interior hunsecker's penthouse}
<A>__{the apartment is dark as susan enters. she does not switch on the lights. she walks through the shadows of the big room, which has a grim and menacing atmosphere. she kicks off her shoes and, hugging the coat about her for warmth walks to the glass windows of the terrace. after a moment she opens them and steps out.}
<L>__{exterior terrace night}
<A>__{susan walks across the terrace. at this height the wind is very strong. camera tracks with the girl, emphasizing the dizzying panorama of new york at night. the girl's manner is strange; she moves as if under compulsion, a sleepwalker. when she reaches the stone parapet, she leans against it with her body slumped, still hugging the fur coat as if it were some protection against her misery.}
